After we bowed our heads in prayer, we went around the table and everyone shared what they were thankful for. 
Beautiful seeing and listening to everyone speak from their heart. Tears, laughter and boundless gratitude. 
Personally, I‚Äôm a little surprised no one expressed how thankful they were that THE Sexiest Man Alive (I refuse to relinquish my title to Blake Shelton or any man) was sitting at the table. I didn‚Äôt want to be a dick and interrupt the prayer, but at some point someones gotta address the elephant in the room. 
Jokes aside, it was a very special Thanksgiving. As my mom pointed out earlier in the day, there was a time back in ‚Äò87 when we couldn‚Äôt even afford Thanksgiving dinner and was praying someone would invite us over their house to eat. We were in a tough spot back then, but we got thru it. 
And here we are today. 
One big, extended, blended, slightly crazy, loving, grateful ohana.

Today, I‚Äôm thankful that this awesome lil‚Äô 5yr old boy, Ty was my special #MakeAWish guest on our #SkyscraperMovie set and I was completely dissed and ignored ü§öüèæüòÇ‚ù§Ô∏è. Ty‚Äôs Wish was to meet the one, the only, demigod himself.. MAUI from Moana. 
So we plan this big trip and meeting. Ty and his beautiful little sister Tia come to set along with his lovely mom and aunty. Ty is SO EXCITED to FINALLY meet his hero, MAUI. He won‚Äôt stop talking, playing and singing his favorite Maui song, You‚Äôre Welcome. 
I put on the MAUI wig, strut in and start singing You‚Äôre Welcome. 
Well, as you see here I walk in, start the song and lil‚Äô Ty takes two long looks at me and decides he‚Äôs gonna treat me like I‚Äôve been stealing his lunch for the last 87 days with the Clint Eastwood glare that says, ‚ÄúIf I were 20yrs older and five feet taller I‚Äôd get up outta this chair and knock that goofy wig off your head punk‚Äù. Best moment ever. 
Always happens like this, even though Ty remained in shock and didn‚Äôt say a word the whole time, the moment I walked away to go back to work, little Ty was SO EXCITED and would NOT STOP TALKING about how he met his best friend MAUI. I‚Äôm also pretty sure he even said how Maui was waaaaayyy better looking and talented in person. 
Hey if Ty‚Äôs happy, then Maui‚Äôs happy. 
Happy Thanksgiving everyone to you and your families. Enjoy your day! 
As always, for me stuff like this will always be the best part of fame. Icy high five disses and all. 
I need a better wig. DJ

I had a blast with this dude @teammarik who blessed our set w/ his presence. 
For those who don‚Äôt know Marik‚Äôs story. He‚Äôs battling cancer and recently placed on hospice. He made a bucket list... and meeting me was on that list. 
So here we are.. I‚Äôm pushing him around set, having fun, introducing him to our crew and explaining to him how our ‚ÄúHollywood magic‚Äù works behind the scenes. 
He had a blast. I was grateful. 
I don‚Äôt know why things happen to kids the way they do. Over the years of spending time with kids and parents who are struggling hard thru disease (often terminal), I‚Äôve realized we just gotta hold onto faith in knowing that there‚Äôs a much bigger and positive reason why this happens. Even if I don‚Äôt understand it at that moment. 
For me, this‚Äôll always be the best part of fame. And the reminder that the most powerful thing we can all do is lead with strong empathy and love. 
It‚Äôs also the reminder to never let yourself get caught up in petty sh*t and keep your thoughts and energy optimistic and big picture. 
So grateful I had a chance to hang with my man Marik aka.. the King of Xbox. 
#MarikAndRock #OnSet #BucketListFun #GratefuMan

Moment we hugged I started getting choked up (manly tears of course:). Hard to even fathom what this mom @teammarik (and so many parents who I meet) is going thru as her son, Marik is fighting the fight of his life. 
What a strong mama with a beautiful heart who‚Äôs beyond blessed with an incredible son who inspires all those around him - including me. 
When she said ‚ÄúGive your kids a hug and cherish every single moment‚Äù.. that one hit home, because it‚Äôs such a reminder to love and hug our loved as hard we can because we never know what tomorrow may bring. 
#MarikAndRock #OnSet #BucketListFun

Here‚Äôs two vids of a bucket list surprise for a very special and awesome 15yr old kid who I just found out was placed in hospice.

This kids fighting like a CHAMP. Can‚Äôt wait to meet you dude.. you got a BIG ROCK SIZE HUG coming your way tomorrow!
